data.content:
Three breaking changes hit your code. Here's each one and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö now takes `Func<>`, not `Expression<Func<>>`

Your expression-tree construction **won't compile** anymore. Replace it with a simple lambda:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

All the `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` machinery is no longer needed.

---

### 2. Complex type columns ŌĆö two changes

**a) Duplicate names are now auto-uniquified.** `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously silently shared one column; now they get `Street` and `Street1`. To keep the old (shared) mapping, pin explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});
```

Or (recommended) let them diverge and **generate a migration** to add the new column.

**b) Nested complex types now use the full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was previously column `BillingAddress_City`; it's now `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. To keep the old name:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

Either way, **create and review a migration** after upgrading ŌĆö these column renames will show up there.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter at the end. Update your signature:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ŌåÉ new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants are redacted
        // unless EnableSensitiveDataLogging is on).
        // Use command.CommandText for the real executed SQL.
    }
}
```

Apply the same change to `CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc. ŌĆö every method on the interface got this parameter.
